Zebra mussels on N. side opposite boat landing
5 Feet tall "ribbon grass" seaweed growing above the water.

new species of tall grass like seaweed- grows above surface of water
zabra mussells have overcome all native clam/snail/crayfish species
light rain about 24 hours ahead of sampling; field work in the watershed started the week of April 29th.
cloudy day- with several rainfall events in the week leading up to the sampling.  Weed beds are becoming more prevelant.

column1: South west part of lake is seeing development occuring along the shoreline.  Other development occuring west of the bridge on the north side of the lake.  No noticable silt fencing between the development and lake.

column2: strong rainfall event in the morning prior to the afternoon sampling.  Additional volunteers: Patty Fairchild and Samantha Molepske
clear day- temperatures in the mid 70's
rain in morning; windy and partly cloudy
mostly sunny day with a few clouds.  Saw a person pull out of the boat landing without cleaning his boat even though there was a washing station less than 20 feet from where he parked - what a shame!
sunny day- leaves are starting to turn
Sunny skies; last sampling of the year
Windy and partly sunny day.  Week proceeding sampling had heavy rains.  Feeder streams into the lake had significant sediment.
cloudy and several rain events the week preceeding sampling
clear sunny day- Patty Fairchild assisted.
